=== Orthostatic Intolerance (Priority)
<subsec:ped-severe-oi>

Orthostatic intolerance (OI) affects 70–90% of pediatric ME/CFS patients, compared to approximately 40–70% of adults @Rowe2017pediatric. This higher prevalence makes OI management the single most important intervention in pediatric ME/CFS. Treatment of orthostatic intolerance improves not only cardiovascular symptoms but also fatigue, cognitive function, and overall wellbeing @Ojha2024pediatricPOTS.

